ystems)<br>- Designing intelligence systems to *enhance* boundary adherence (e.g., AGIs that throttle compute during grid stress) | Intelligence cannot thrive in isolation. Violating kinship guarantees *self-collapse*:<br>- An AI ignoring water boundaries → data-center overheating → system failure<br>- Humans ignoring soil microbes → malnutrition → cognitive decline<br>- Algorithms eroding democratic trust → inability to coordinate boundary adherence<br>**Kinship isn’t charity—it’s the substrate of adaptive agency.** |  
