> **Reese’s Revision**: **Add as Foundation 5: True-Cost Accounting as the First Boundary**  
> *No action—whether innovation, policy, or practice—may be taken if its *total social cost* (private cost + externalized harms) exceeds the *total social value* of the next-best alternative. This constraint overrides all other foundations when economics is at stake.*  
> *Verification*: Mandatory **True-Cost Impact Assessment (TCIA)** for all boundary-relevant decisions (e.g., wetland restoration, AI deployment, agricultural policy), measuring:  
